Subject: RE: [T2] Securing Pedal Pan on '69

Thanks to all for the tips on the bolt sizing. I got a few at the hardware
store - unfortunately even a size 14 sheet metal screw does not really grab
tightly.so I ordered some size 17 online from McMaster.

 

I was able to use a few 13mm bolts where there is a threaded connection. One
of the original bolts snapped off, so I'm trying to drill that out
carefully. I'll be using some anti-seize on the new stuff.

 

I've also discovered some other stuff that needs work up front.this never
seems to end. ;)

 

